#. Max bytes: 511
msgctxt "Offset_0x464_Len_511"
msgid "The Events of Yakuza 2\n\nDecember, 2006. Kazuma Kiryu became the legendary yakuza who had\nascended to the Tojo Clan's fourth chairman and retired the same day.\n\nBut in the wake of the ten billion yen incident, the Tojo Clan weakened,\nhaving lost its most prominent leaders in the turmoil.\n\nThe eye of the Omi Alliance, western Japan's largest yakuza organization,\nturned east. To avoid an all-out war, the Tojo Clan's fifth chairman,\nYukio Terada, told Kiryu of a plan to broker peace with the Omi.\n\nHowever... \n"
msgstr ""

#. Max bytes: 505
msgctxt "Offset_0x1224_Len_505"
msgid "The Events of Yakuza 2\n\nRyuji ignited his coup with his own father as the kindling.\nAs negotiations between Kiryu and Goda began, Ryuji's Go-Ryu Clan\ninfiltrated the proceedings, laying bare his desire to conquer\nthe world of the yakuza.\n\nForced into cooperation with the police, Kiryu began working alongside\nKaoru Sayama from the Osaka PD's 4th Division to stop Ryuji Goda. Through\nthis alliance, it became apparent that a tragedy that occurred over 20 years\nago in Kamurocho was connected to them both."
msgstr ""

#. Max bytes: 511
msgctxt "Offset_0x1674_Len_511"
msgid "The Events of Yakuza 2\n\nThe Jingweon Mafia, a Korean mainland crime syndicate, was all but\nwiped out in a raid organized by Sohei Dojima in the early 1980s.\n\nUnder Dojima's orders, it was none other than Shintaro Kazama, the\nman who raised Kiryu, who led the raid.\n\nBut there were survivors, including a very young Ryuji Goda...\n\nThe survivors of the massacre desired nothing but revenge, and over\n20 years later, the opportunity arose in the chance to envelop the\nTojo Clan in an all-out east-versus-west war.\n"
msgstr ""

#. Max bytes: 473
msgctxt "Offset_0x1AD4_Len_473"
msgid "The Events of Yakuza 2\n\nOne of the massacre's survivors was in fact Yukio Terada, who had\nstaged his death in order to set the plot in motion. But to Terada,\nrevenge was both his destiny and his burden...\n\nAs the events of the massacre came to light, Kaoru Sayama discovered\nthat she was actually the half-sister of Ryuji Goda. But as the bonds\nof blood thickened, so too, did it spill. Kiryu stood in the center\nof the pool, seeking to end the cycle of hatred and revenge."
msgstr ""

#. Max bytes: 365
msgctxt "Offset_0x1F14_Len_365"
msgid "The Events of Yakuza 2\n\nIt was only Ryuji Goda who fought not for blood, but for pride.\nHe wanted nothing more than to surpass the legendary yakuza and\nbecome the sole surviving dragon.\n\n\"There's only room for one dragon in this world.\"\n \nWith the schemers and conspirators of the Jingweon plot bleeding out\nof the picture, Kiryu and Ryuji prepared for a showdown.\n"
msgstr ""

#. Max bytes: 239
msgctxt "Offset_0x22E4_Len_239"
msgid "The Events of Yakuza 2\n\nThe two dragons roared as they threw themselves into an all-out battle\nfor supremacy.\n\nIt was Ryuji who finally fell.\n\nThe war of east versus west fell silent as the conflict between two\ndragons decided its fate...\n"
msgstr ""

